    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by way of its scale, massing, location and design, would result in an incongruous and discordant form of development to the detriment of the character and appearance of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;ubject property, adjoining terrace and the wider Stoke Newington Reservoirs, Filter Beds and New River Conservation Area and Brownswood Conservation Area. The proposal is considered contrary to the NPPF, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;Heritage conservation and growth) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the London Plan 2021, and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
